; TUPLECMP simplification, non-equality assert path: both sides of A < B
; become the same value (constant 1 from a fact, and a fused X/X column from
; the message clause), so every pair is dropped as trivially equal. A
; zero-pair kLessThan compare is vacuously false and must be replaced by its
; false_body; p stays empty in every mode.

#message m(i32 X).

#local bar(i32 A, i32 B).
bar(1, 1).
bar(X, X) : m(X).

#query p(free i32 A).
p(A) : bar(A, B), A < B.

#query all_bar(free i32 A, free i32 B).
all_bar(A, B) : bar(A, B).
